article_title: KC is competing in White House challenge on Affordable Care Act sign-ups
article_text:
Twenty cities get the Healthy Communities Challenge

The prize is a visit from the president

In KC area, 112,000 uninsured people are eligible for marketplace plans

article_metadata.news-keywords: Healthy Communities Challenge, KC, Kansas City, White House, Affordable Care Act, Obamacare, health, insurance, signup, enroll, care
article_metadata.description: The White House announced that it has issued a Healthy Communities Challenge to Kansas City and 19 other cities to see which can make the most progress in enrolling eligible people in Affordable Care Act marketplace insurance plans.
